{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Live-store remediation: drive fsck to zero (safe, reversible, batched, committed)\n\n## Why\n`rebar fsck` on the live store = 2422 SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT + 11 ORPHAN_EVENT + 1 MISSING_CREATE. Fix #1 stopped\nnew corruption; this cleans the backlog. DESTRUCTIVE on a live, git-backed shared store — safety is first-class.\nConsumes NEW sibling deliverables: A1 (tricolour-head-ratfish) ADDS the `.retired` rename + `RETIRED_SUFFIX` +\nretire helper; A2 (glandulous-potent-waxwing) ADDS the `include_retired` rebuild path. depends_on A1+A2.\n\n## Repair per fault class\n- SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT (2422): a folded source file STILL PRESENT (listed in `source_event_uuids`, never deleted).\n  Repair = call A1's retire helper to rename each still-present listed source to `.retired`. NOT a rebuild.\n- ORPHAN_EVENT (11): a pre-snapshot event absent from `source_event_uuids`. Routed BY EVENT TYPE (see policy):\n  AUTO-RECOVER types -> A2's `reduce_ticket(..., include_retired=True)` rebuild; HUMAN-TRIAGE types -> surfaced,\n  NOT auto-rebuilt (the rebuild would pick an order that may be wrong).\n- MISSING_CREATE (1): `fsck --repair` logs it, no automatic write; human triage.\n\n## Orphan disposition (a CODE constant, not just prose)\nDefine two sets in code (enumerating ALL KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES so none is unclassified):\n- AUTO-RECOVER (additive/commutative): COMMENT, LINK, UNLINK, TAG_DELTA, COMMITS, BRIDGE_ALERT, REVERT.\n- HUMAN-TRIAGE (order-sensitive): STATUS, EDIT, FILE_IMPACT, VERIFY_COMMANDS, SIGNATURE, WORKFLOW_RUN,\n  WORKFLOW_STEP, ARCHIVED. Decisions recorded in the PR / a linked ops doc.\n\n## Safety\n- GIT-AWARE writes: the tracker is a git worktree. Each batch commits+pushes:\n  `git -C <tracker> add -A && git -C <tracker> commit -m 'a3-remediation: batch N/M' && git -C <tracker> push`.\n  If a push FAILS (conflict/network/reject), ABORT the run and surface the error — do NOT continue; the pre-tag\n  enables rollback. BEFORE any write: `git -C <tracker> tag pre-a3-remediation <oid>`; rollback = `git reset --hard\n  pre-a3-remediation && git push --force-with-lease`.\n- Dry-run FIRST: `fsck --repair --dry-run` prints per-ticket before/after diff + dispositions, writes NOTHING\n  (a test asserts zero file writes + zero commits); the live run is gated on human review.\n- Reconciler pause: disable the `reconcile-bridge.yml` GHA schedule for the window via the GitHub API/CLI\n  (`gh workflow disable reconcile-bridge.yml`), verify no pass is mid-flight, and RE-ENABLE in a `finally`/failsafe\n  (auto re-enable after N minutes or on repair-process exit) so a crash never leaves it disabled. (The pass-lock\n  `refs/reconciler/lock` is a leased CAS lock and would expire, so it is NOT the pause mechanism.) Manual writers\n  hold off (documented); the batched+committed+pre-tagged design makes a stray write recoverable.\n- Idempotent/resumable: fsck itself is the AUTHORITATIVE resumability check (re-run repairs only tickets fsck still\n  flags). A per-ticket `.a3-repaired` marker is a LOCAL, gitignored optimization only. Per-snapshot rewrite uses the\n  EXISTING `rebar._store.fsutil.atomic_write` (not hand-rolled). The SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT rename + rebuild hold the\n  store write-lock for the per-ticket critical section (no TOCTOU with a concurrent writer). Per-ticket failure\n  logs+skips (no batch abort). Batched `--limit=200`, wait >=30s between.\n\n## Scope\n`_commands/fsck.py` ONLY (`--repair`/`--dry-run`/`--limit`, per-batch git commit+push, disposition constants,\nper-snapshot `fsutil.atomic_write`, local marker, write-lock critical section; update the `fsck --help` golden files\n`tests/golden/cli_help/fsck__help.out` + the `-h` variant). This ticket does NOT edit `compact.py` (A1 owns all\ncompact.py changes) — it CALLS A1's retire helper and A2's `include_retired` rebuild. Gated on RC1 fix #1.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `fsck --repair --dry-run` prints per-ticket before/after + dispositions; a test asserts ZERO file writes and ZERO commits in dry-run.\n- [ ] Live repair commits+pushes each batch; a push failure ABORTS + surfaces the error; pre-tag created; rollback rehearsed on a fixture (post-rollback store == pre-tag state).\n- [ ] Reconciler paused by `gh workflow disable` (verified no in-flight pass), re-enabled in a failsafe `finally`.\n- [ ] Orphan disposition is a code constant covering ALL KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES; AUTO-RECOVER rebuilt, HUMAN-TRIAGE surfaced (not auto-rebuilt); tested.\n- [ ] Resumability via fsck re-check; `.a3-repaired` marker local/gitignored; per-snapshot rewrite uses `fsutil.atomic_write`; write-lock held per ticket; crash-before-marker is safe (test).\n- [ ] Synthetic-fixture unit tests: SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT / ORPHAN_EVENT (both dispositions) / MISSING_CREATE (incl. `.retired`) repair correctly.\n- [ ] Live store reaches 0 UNRESOLVED faults (triaged+documented orphans count as resolved); before/after counts recorded.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783480659816861001,"uuid":"f146956b-3af3-4501-95c7-ca4cee944660"}